UPI Safety: Never enter your UPI PIN to receive money; a PIN is only required to send or pay.


UPI Safety: Treat your UPI PIN like your ATM PIN—never share it with anyone over the phone or text.


Check URLs: Always look for "https://" and the padlock icon before entering credentials on any website.


Strong Passwords: Use a unique, complex password for your college email and change it every semester.


Enable 2FA: Activate Two-Factor Authentication on all social media and banking apps.


Think Before Clicking: Avoid clicking links in emails or SMS that claim you have won a "lottery" or "scholarship".

Verify Sellers: When buying/selling online, only use trusted platforms and avoid taking the conversation to private chat apps.


Official Reporting: If defrauded, immediately report the incident at cybercrime.gov.in or call the National Helpline 1930
